heir stake in Investor and Providentia to prevent any raid on the heart of their business empire But analysts say the Wallenbergs position in the electrical engineering firm ASEA AB ltASEA ST is also too small at 126 pct of the voting rights and there has been growing speculation that the group will be forced to sell off fringe interests to protect its core activities
